\item {\tt mailgrp}: 1 if they were sent mail encouraging them to vote; 0 otherwise\vspace{-.1in}
\item {\tt ward}: voting ward of household $(2, 3, \ldots, 30)$\vspace{-.1in}
\item {\tt appeal}: Type of appeal (1, 2, 3)\vspace{-.1in}
\item {\tt mail}: Number of mailings sent (0,1,2,3)\vspace{-.1in}
\end{itemize}

You notice that mailings have no significant effect on turnout.  Yet, pretend you are a less-than-scrupulous purveyor of campaign mailings.  You get your hand on Gerber and Green's data, and do the following:

\begin{itemize}
